**Summary:** Manusmriti chapter 7 in the corpus (86 verses) addresses war-related duties dispersed through the chapter rather than in a dedicated section. Manu says the Kshatriya king must protect the world justly (7.2), be "very severe towards his enemies" (7.32), deliberate with ministers on "peace and war" (7.56), rely on envoys to make and break alliances (7.65–66), and maintain strong fortifications — with the hill-fort supreme, where one archer can hold off a hundred men (7.71–74). The corpus chapter ends at verse 86; detailed tactical war rules (which appear later in the classical text) are not present in this portion.
